Acerinox, EDP-Energias, Portugal Telecom: Iberian Equity Preview

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-03-04T05:00:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/acerinox-edp-energias-portugal-telecom-iberian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Spanish and Portuguese trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses and share prices are from the
previous close.    Spain ’s IBEX 35 slipped 0.7 percent to 10,566.9. Portugal’s  PSI-20 Index (PSI20)  retreated 0.3 percent to 7,947.62.  Spanish stocks:    Acerinox SA (ACX)  : The stainless steel producer’s board
agreed to pay a second 2010 gross interim dividend of 10 euro
cents per share on April 5, the company said in a regulatory
filing. The shares advanced 0.9 percent to 13.78 euros.    Gestevision Telecinco SA (TL5)  (TL5 SM): Spain’s largest
commercial television station was rated “buy” in new coverage
at Berenberg Bank. The shares fell 1.1 percent to 8.83 euros.    Solaria Energia y Medio Ambiente SA (SLR)  : The Spanish
solar-cell manufacturer got a 12.7 million-euro loan to finance
a plant in  Germany , the Spanish company said in a filing to
regulators. The shares were unchanged at 1.64 euros.  Portuguese stocks:  EDP-Energias de Portugal SA (EDP PL): Portugal’s biggest
power company said full-year net income rose 5.4 percent to 1.08
billion euros. The company aims to raise 500 million euros in
asset sales this year. The stock advanced 0.6 percent to close
at 2.79 euros in Lisbon before the earnings announcement.    Portugal Telecom SGPS SA (PTC)  : Portugal’s biggest phone
company’s unit in Namibia said it opposes a move to force
mobile-phone companies to charge the same rates when subscribers
call other networks in the southern African nation. The shares
dropped 0.6 percent to 8.38 euros. 